body: Can you open the "Yolact" model using Netron (https://github.com/lutzroeder/Netron, https://netron.app/) and verify if there are two nodes with the same name? (Ctrl+F to search by name) If two nodes really do have the same name, then I'm unsure why CPU/CUDA execution providers work fine (maybe one node is optimized away somehow?), but it's a model bug if two nodes have the same name. Alternately, do you have a link to the converted .onnx model file? Thanks.

> Can you open the "Yolact" model using Netron (https://github.com/lutzroeder/Netron, https://netron.app/) and verify if there are two nodes with the same name? If two nodes really do have the same name, then I'm unsure why CPU/CUDA execution providers work fine (maybe one node is optimized away somehow?), but it would definitely be a model bug if two nodes have the same name. Alternately, do you have a link to the converted .onnx model file? Thanks.

I have open the model using Netron, no nodes have the same name. Here is the model i used [model_yolact.rar](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mrljwlm/hellow-world/master/model_yolact.rar)

I found that when i disable the GraphOptimization using the below code, it will be OK
`session_options.SetGraphOptimizationLevel(GraphOptimizationLevel::ORT_DISABLE_ALL);`

Thanks for sharing the model. Hmm, I'm not encountering any issues running it via [WinMLRunner](https://github.com/Microsoft/Windows-Machine-Learning/tree/master/Tools/WinMLRunner) with ORT master (and I doubt the issue would be anything C# specific). There may have been fixes since ORT 1.6 ðŸ¤”. Have you tried running it with ORT 1.8.2?

I'm having the same issue in ORT 1.9.0.  In my case the model is a slightly modified YOLOX model converted to onnx with the pytorch convert.  Works great on CPU, but claims there is a duplicated node name when I try to run on DirectML.  Works if I turn off optimizations.  There are 2 or 3 other issues on github with similar problems, so I think this is a real bug.

@mrljwlm, @jbrownkramer  : Heads up, we have a pending fix for YoloV4, which very likely also applies to YoloX. https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/9929/files. It won't make ORT 1.10.0 release though, meaning it would need to be compiled from master (or possibly a 1.10.1 patch release). Thank you for reporting.
I'm having the same problem in 1.10.0 release  dml_provider.  cuda  cpu is working well. When will the next release be?

@esawudi: Historically ORT releases (just looking at the releases page) have been every 2-3 months, but there might be a point release of 1.10.1. If so, we'll tag this PR with `rel-1.10.1` for the ONNX Runtime team to see (@faxu on ORT might know). Building source from master is an option too.
